Explanation:
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/58c720ed-0429-42e0-8590-04d9022b0caa_1604770737.4726672.png)


For each node:
1. Connect left child of its left child with right child of its left child (green)
2. Connect right child of its left child with left child of its right child (blue)
3. Connect left child of its right child with right child of its right child (red)
4. Connect left child to the right child (black)

Main trick is that we iterate over two subtrees at the same time (left and right). This trivializes whole problem into four cases mentioned above. 
For base case we check if left node is null, since we can't link null node. Due to the fact that trees are guaranteed to be perfectly balanced, we might as well check if right node is null. It doesn't matter.

