Checking for all appropriate digits to be included in the ans, if it's not the last digit of the ans list, then merging this digit with the list returned by the fututre calls for this particular digit and return the final list for this particular call.

If it's the last digit (i.e. k == 1) and the digit is appropriate acc to the PS then just add this in a list of list of Integer and return else return empty list.

'last fn var' is just keeping the value of last used digit for this particular fn call.

```
class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> combinationSum3(int k, int n) {
        return helper(n, k, 0);
    }

    public List<List<Integer>> helper(int n, int k, int last){
        List<List<Integer>> temp2 = new ArrayList<>();

        if(last >= n || (k == 1 && n >= 10)) return temp2;
        if(k == 1 && n > last){
            List<Integer> temp = new ArrayList<>();
            temp.add(n);
            temp2.add(temp);
            return temp2;
        }

        for(int i = last + 1; i < n && i < 10; i++){
            List<List<Integer>> curr = helper(n - i, k - 1, i);
            if(!curr.isEmpty()){
                for(List<Integer> ins : curr){
                    List<Integer> temp3 = new ArrayList<>();
                    temp3.add(i);
                    temp3.addAll(ins);
                    temp2.add(temp3);
                }
            }
        }

        return temp2;
    }
}
```

